Learning Theory
Hypothesis Testing
Q1: What are the 5 steps:
// Step 1: State null and alternative hypothesis //
// Step 2: Select a level of significance //
// Step 3: Identify test statistic //
// Step 4: Formulate decision rule//
// Step 5: Take a sample, and arrive at a decision//

Q2A: Null Hypothesis (Ho)
// State there is no difference between parameter and specific value //
Q2B: Alternative Hypothesis (H1)
// State there is an existence value between the parameter and specific value //

Q3: Type of test
// a) 1-tailed test: left_tailed and right-tailed //
//    - Ho should be rejected when the test value is a critical region on one side of the mean //
// b) 2-tailed test //
//    - Ho should be registered when the test value is in either of the 2 critical regions//

Q4: Level of significance
// Max probability of committing a type error //
// 0.10(10%), 0.05(5%), 0.01(1%) //

Q5: Formula

Quiz
Q1: Type 1 error
H0 true but reject
Q2: Type 2 error
H0 false but accept
